I'm trying to go again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's only Monday.
It is already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get medical clearance, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will take VERY long and mean a LOT of extra work.
This is somewhat discouraging, but still just another problem that has to be solved. So far, it seems manageable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what lies ahead for me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely do not grant medical clearance if one takes medication for it.
